“The Mother DAO” works by replicating the original Ataraxc DAO in a process akin to Hilbert’s paradox of the infinite hotel. Each subsequent DAO created under the "Mega-chain" will be maximized for demand and value, making initial investors the most rewarded. This process can continue infinitely, leading to growth and expansion of the Ataraxc ecosystem.
The benefit of this scaling model for investors is that it allows them to participate in large-scale investments with minimal risk. The value of the Ataraxc DAO is constantly increasing, which acts as a stable base point for the ARXX token. The token's value will also increase as more businesses are created and operated within the Ataraxc ecosystem, accepting only the ARXX token as a means of exchange.
Another innovation to consider is, Proof of transaction, or PoT, is a consensus mechanism that aims to maintain the security and integrity of a blockchain network by rewarding the most active participants, rather than computational power as in proof of work. In the context of the Bitcoin protocol, PoT would work by considering the frequency and size of transactions made by a user as a measure of their activity and influence on the network. This activity would then be weighted and used as a factor in determining which users get to validate transactions and add blocks to the blockchain. As a result, PoT reduces the reliance on computational power as a means of securing the network and could potentially lead to more efficient and sustainable blockchain systems.
By utilizing proof of transaction as the core backing of the cryptocurrency, Ataraxc eliminates the need for traditional blockchain mining methods. Instead, validators are employed at a fraction of the cost to keep the blockchain ledger updated. This not only reduces energy consumption, but also leads to a more efficient and cost-effective financial ecosystem.
